1
00:00:29,620 --> 00:00:32,980
=The Secret of the Lost Pearl=

2
00:00:33,020 --> 00:00:34,940
=Episode 6=
(Fiction. Do not imitate.)

3
00:00:43,030 --> 00:00:44,000
- Run!
- Move!

4
00:00:47,390 --> 00:00:48,960
Run! The Cadaver Worms are coming!

5
00:00:58,880 --> 00:01:00,430
Go! Keep going!

6
00:01:11,430 --> 00:01:12,870
Run! Hurry!

7
00:01:13,590 --> 00:01:15,070
Go! Move! Run!

8
00:01:15,920 --> 00:01:17,870
Drop the rope ladder! Now!

9
00:01:18,560 --> 00:01:19,790
Go, go, go!

10
00:01:19,790 --> 00:01:22,040
Hurry up, hurry up!

11
00:01:23,870 --> 00:01:25,240
Go! Move!

12
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:27,040
Hurry, He Shutong!

13
00:01:28,510 --> 00:01:29,360
Faster, Shutong!

14
00:01:29,430 --> 00:01:30,270
Come on, hurry!

15
00:01:31,150 --> 00:01:31,990
Go now!

16
00:01:35,870 --> 00:01:36,710
Move!

17
00:01:38,790 --> 00:01:39,640
Go, go, go!

18
00:01:46,950 --> 00:01:48,680
Hurry! Hurry!

19
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:50,150
- Move!
- Go!

20
00:01:50,680 --> 00:01:52,200
Hurry! Hurry!

21
00:01:52,200 --> 00:01:53,040
Hurry.

22
00:01:53,200 --> 00:01:54,040
Come on, hurry.

23
00:01:54,560 --> 00:01:56,870
- Get up!
- Faster!

24
00:02:03,870 --> 00:02:05,430
Qiang, get up, faster!

25
00:02:05,870 --> 00:02:06,710
Hurry!

26
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:11,280
- Qiang!
- Qiang!

27
00:02:12,520 --> 00:02:13,360
Faster!

28
00:02:15,190 --> 00:02:16,080
Help me!

29
00:02:16,080 --> 00:02:17,560
- Qiang!
- Qiang!

30
00:02:17,750 --> 00:02:18,590
Qiang!

31
00:02:20,560 --> 00:02:24,750
- Qiang!
- Qiang!

32
00:02:25,240 --> 00:02:26,080
Grenade!

33
00:02:42,840 --> 00:02:45,560
Great, now we need another way in.

34
00:03:10,360 --> 00:03:11,200
Is there

35
00:03:11,680 --> 00:03:13,120
any other hidden entrance?

36
00:03:25,840 --> 00:03:27,080
Find the entrance,

37
00:03:27,280 --> 00:03:28,200
and you can walk free.

38
00:03:33,960 --> 00:03:36,240
Builders used to leave a way out

39
00:03:36,240 --> 00:03:37,520
after finishing the tomb,

40
00:03:37,870 --> 00:03:39,590
lest they be trapped alive inside.

41
00:03:39,870 --> 00:03:41,840
It's pretty well hidden.

42
00:03:42,840 --> 00:03:43,710
Where could it be?

43
00:03:45,870 --> 00:03:47,680
The temple was built as cover

44
00:03:47,750 --> 00:03:48,840
to avoid tome raiders.

45
00:03:49,150 --> 00:03:51,310
But why would the tomb keeper
live so far away

46
00:03:51,590 --> 00:03:52,790
and build his home in a valley

47
00:03:53,030 --> 00:03:54,710
so far from the tomb's entrance?

48
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:55,910
That's true.

49
00:03:56,630 --> 00:03:59,310
If someone tried to get into the temple,

50
00:03:59,870 --> 00:04:02,400
he'd be too far to stop them, right?

51
00:04:02,400 --> 00:04:03,750
By the time the tomb raiders go in,

52
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:05,173
he couldn't do anything about it.

53
00:04:06,430 --> 00:04:08,000
Since he's been living there all along,

54
00:04:08,360 --> 00:04:09,240
his house must have

55
00:04:09,240 --> 00:04:11,280
something really worth guarding.

56
00:04:14,470 --> 00:04:16,510
If that's the case, his place

57
00:04:16,510 --> 00:04:17,870
could actually be an entrance.

58
00:04:43,630 --> 00:04:44,470
The backyard.

59
00:04:49,750 --> 00:04:51,120
Lu, help me look around.

60
00:04:51,120 --> 00:04:52,120
Stop just sitting there.

61
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:57,840
What's going on?

62
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:03,973
Careful, everyone.
There are mines in the garden.

63
00:05:05,830 --> 00:05:06,800
Mines?

64
00:05:07,160 --> 00:05:08,240
Good news.

65
00:05:09,040 --> 00:05:09,950
The mines mean

66
00:05:10,240 --> 00:05:12,000
there's a tomb entrance nearby.

67
00:05:12,510 --> 00:05:14,040
Get someone to clear them.

68
00:05:14,920 --> 00:05:16,920
Why are you all just standing there?

69
00:05:17,390 --> 00:05:18,230
You can't do it?

70
00:05:19,240 --> 00:05:20,510
You guys are unbelievably slow.

71
00:05:20,520 --> 00:05:21,390
Back in the day,

72
00:05:21,390 --> 00:05:23,310
when I was in the army
with Commander Chen,

73
00:05:23,560 --> 00:05:24,800
I led the demining team.

74
00:05:24,992 --> 00:05:26,259
Triggered mines, pressure mines,

75
00:05:26,270 --> 00:05:27,542
scattered mines, bouncing mines.

76
00:05:27,553 --> 00:05:29,190
I could clear them all in minutes.

77
00:05:31,310 --> 00:05:32,870
Since you're so brave,

78
00:05:34,190 --> 00:05:35,070
everyone, fall back.

79
00:05:35,870 --> 00:05:37,070
We'll leave it to you.

80
00:05:38,380 --> 00:05:39,240
Wait.

81
00:05:39,360 --> 00:05:42,190
That unit runs with clear divisions.

82
00:05:42,800 --> 00:05:44,160
Commander Chen handles demining.

83
00:05:44,480 --> 00:05:46,390
I take the lead position.

84
00:05:47,190 --> 00:05:48,190
Right, Commander Chen?

85
00:05:49,040 --> 00:05:50,000
Comrade Li Ke,

86
00:05:50,630 --> 00:05:52,240
if you hadn't brought it up,

87
00:05:52,310 --> 00:05:54,680
we would've been resting
on the sleeper train.

88
00:05:54,950 --> 00:05:56,160
But I've said it.

89
00:05:56,160 --> 00:05:57,630
You can't let me lose face here.

90
00:05:57,630 --> 00:05:58,630
Have you made a decision?

91
00:05:59,360 --> 00:06:00,550
He's never served in the army.

92
00:06:03,040 --> 00:06:05,600
Even a militia counts as soldiers.

93
00:06:06,526 --> 00:06:08,000
A mandarin still counts as an orange.

94
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:08,950
Go away.

95
00:06:10,560 --> 00:06:11,400
Give me the knife.

96
00:06:13,430 --> 00:06:14,270
The rope.

97
00:06:30,480 --> 00:06:31,630
Commander Chen, be careful!

98
00:07:05,560 --> 00:07:06,430
Give me a marker.

99
00:07:06,920 --> 00:07:07,920
A marker.

100
00:07:08,360 --> 00:07:09,830
Hurry. Any red flags?

101
00:07:10,390 --> 00:07:11,240
You don't have them?

102
00:07:11,240 --> 00:07:12,630
We have them.

103
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:14,040
Look at us here.

104
00:07:14,390 --> 00:07:15,230
Coming.

105
00:07:15,390 --> 00:07:16,630
Something red?

106
00:07:17,190 --> 00:07:18,950
Come on.

107
00:07:19,360 --> 00:07:20,270
Don't run around.

108
00:07:20,920 --> 00:07:23,360
Chen, there are no red flags.

109
00:07:23,720 --> 00:07:25,270
Use something yellow instead.

110
00:07:34,510 --> 00:07:35,800
Chen, you're fearless,

111
00:07:35,830 --> 00:07:37,920
clearing mines with just a stick.

112
00:07:38,600 --> 00:07:40,059
Using firecrackers to take down jets,

113
00:07:40,070 --> 00:07:41,293
you're truly something else.

114
00:07:43,920 --> 00:07:44,760
I'll be careful.

115
00:08:16,920 --> 00:08:17,800
I found it.

116
00:08:17,920 --> 00:08:19,560
See? I told you.

117
00:08:19,680 --> 00:08:21,270
I knew there was an entrance here.

118
00:08:21,600 --> 00:08:23,040
Commander Chen, well done.

119
00:08:23,430 --> 00:08:24,270
Let's go.

120
00:08:40,510 --> 00:08:41,870
A big eye again.

121
00:08:43,120 --> 00:08:43,960
Yeah.

122
00:08:51,670 --> 00:08:52,510
Listen to me.

123
00:08:52,790 --> 00:08:54,240
This has to be the entrance.

124
00:08:54,720 --> 00:08:56,080
See? I've got instincts.

125
00:08:56,550 --> 00:08:57,390
Move aside.

126
00:09:01,550 --> 00:09:02,750
Boss, there's space down here.

127
00:09:05,840 --> 00:09:07,240
We've found the tomb passage

128
00:09:08,320 --> 00:09:09,320
and cleared the mines.

129
00:09:09,720 --> 00:09:12,000
I've done my part. Good luck to you.

130
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:12,870
We're leaving.

131
00:09:13,200 --> 00:09:14,080
Let's go.

132
00:09:14,080 --> 00:09:14,920
Hold on.

133
00:09:15,550 --> 00:09:16,840
If I let you go now,

134
00:09:16,870 --> 00:09:18,000
you'll go call the cops.

135
00:09:18,150 --> 00:09:19,790
Besides, you've come this far.

136
00:09:19,790 --> 00:09:22,150
Don't you wanna take a look inside?

137
00:09:22,910 --> 00:09:24,630
I've seen things I should

138
00:09:24,630 --> 00:09:25,600
and shouldn't see.

139
00:09:26,260 --> 00:09:27,453
After running around all day,

140
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:28,660
I almost forgot to ask you.

141
00:09:29,270 --> 00:09:30,803
Does the scar on your back still hurt?

142
00:09:42,150 --> 00:09:44,720
Why's everyone staring at me?

143
00:09:44,750 --> 00:09:45,750
I didn't tell her.

144
00:09:46,150 --> 00:09:46,990
Lu can vouch for it.

145
00:09:48,960 --> 00:09:50,480
The veins on the chest are bulging.

146
00:09:50,600 --> 00:09:52,480
They've probably spread
below the collarbone.

147
00:09:53,150 --> 00:09:54,720
You wanna know how I found out?

148
00:10:08,670 --> 00:10:09,720
Chen,

149
00:10:10,440 --> 00:10:12,120
I've heard a lot about you.

150
00:10:12,770 --> 00:10:14,783
You went through quite the hassle
to lure me here.

151
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:16,080
Who are you?

152
00:10:16,320 --> 00:10:17,960
That doesn't matter.

153
00:10:18,320 --> 00:10:23,030
But I've got an eye-shaped scar
on my back too.

154
00:10:23,150 --> 00:10:25,390
It started with that scar on the back.

155
00:10:25,720 --> 00:10:29,200
Then the veins began
to swell up in the chest.

156
00:10:29,360 --> 00:10:31,910
After that, the veins hardened.

157
00:10:31,960 --> 00:10:33,080
This illness can be treated?

158
00:10:33,670 --> 00:10:36,960
Modern medicine can ease the pain,

159
00:10:36,960 --> 00:10:38,670
but only for a short while.

160
00:10:38,840 --> 00:10:41,960
To truly heal,
you can only rely on yourself.

161
00:10:42,080 --> 00:10:43,953
Right now, I just want
to go home and lie down.

162
00:10:44,080 --> 00:10:45,480
Sleep cures everything.

163
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:52,790
Chen, why keep fooling yourself?

164
00:10:53,870 --> 00:10:55,630
I know you're not afraid of dying.

165
00:10:55,840 --> 00:10:56,680
But

166
00:10:56,870 --> 00:10:59,630
if you don't take action this time,

167
00:10:59,790 --> 00:11:00,750
do you really think

168
00:11:01,200 --> 00:11:03,200
those few friends of yours

169
00:11:03,600 --> 00:11:05,630
will make it out alive?

170
00:12:10,720 --> 00:12:11,560
Chen,

171
00:12:11,571 --> 00:12:13,139
I didn't even get the chance to ask you.

172
00:12:13,150 --> 00:12:14,670
What exactly was said on that call?

173
00:12:15,360 --> 00:12:17,080
It worked better than my advice.

174
00:12:17,550 --> 00:12:19,270
What made you change your mind
so suddenly?

175
00:12:19,630 --> 00:12:20,790
He's right.

176
00:12:21,030 --> 00:12:22,080
Dying isn't the problem,

177
00:12:23,510 --> 00:12:25,240
but dying without knowing why is.

178
00:12:26,480 --> 00:12:28,120
Alright, whatever you do,

179
00:12:28,240 --> 00:12:29,440
I've got your back.

180
00:13:01,510 --> 00:13:02,729
Do you know what that's called?

181
00:13:02,740 --> 00:13:03,600
No.

182
00:13:03,720 --> 00:13:04,960
A tomb guardian beast.

183
00:13:06,270 --> 00:13:07,440
Common in tombs.

184
00:13:07,870 --> 00:13:09,840
It keeps away evil spirits inside,

185
00:13:10,150 --> 00:13:12,080
so the tomb owner can rest undisturbed.

186
00:13:12,816 --> 00:13:13,899
It started in the Chu tombs

187
00:13:13,910 --> 00:13:16,630
during the Warring States.

188
00:13:17,080 --> 00:13:19,960
It thrived through Wei, Jin,
Sui, and Tang.

189
00:13:20,080 --> 00:13:21,840
By the Five Dynasties, they dropped it.

190
00:13:22,150 --> 00:13:24,000
They came up with new designs.

191
00:13:26,120 --> 00:13:27,000
Beautiful.

192
00:13:27,510 --> 00:13:28,550
Really beautiful.

193
00:13:33,030 --> 00:13:34,000
Trap!

194
00:13:34,510 --> 00:13:35,350
Get down!

195
00:13:49,480 --> 00:13:50,840
- Lu!
- Lu!

196
00:14:00,360 --> 00:14:01,200
Chen!

197
00:14:01,200 --> 00:14:02,040
Chen Youxi!

198
00:14:08,150 --> 00:14:09,200
Are you okay?

199
00:14:10,720 --> 00:14:11,670
I'm fine.

200
00:14:17,270 --> 00:14:18,110
Rope!

201
00:14:19,200 --> 00:14:20,150
Hey, Commander Chen.

202
00:14:20,750 --> 00:14:22,443
You got hit
right after entering the tomb?

203
00:14:22,720 --> 00:14:24,080
That's not your usual style.

204
00:14:24,150 --> 00:14:26,630
Now's not the time for jokes.

205
00:14:26,910 --> 00:14:29,200
When do we not fall into pits
during digs?

206
00:14:29,360 --> 00:14:30,750
No need to make a fuss about it.

207
00:14:30,750 --> 00:14:32,360
Cut the talk and pull me up now.

208
00:14:33,480 --> 00:14:35,200
Chen Youxi, catch this.

209
00:14:43,120 --> 00:14:44,080
Pull me up.

210
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:46,840
Wait a sec.

211
00:14:47,510 --> 00:14:48,390
What's wrong?

212
00:14:52,390 --> 00:14:53,840
I found a dried corpse.

213
00:14:54,240 --> 00:14:55,440
There's a hole beside it.

214
00:14:57,150 --> 00:14:58,320
A corpse?

215
00:14:58,630 --> 00:14:59,510
What kind of hole?

216
00:15:00,080 --> 00:15:01,480
It looks neatly carved.

217
00:15:01,870 --> 00:15:03,200
But I'm not sure where it leads.

218
00:15:04,030 --> 00:15:05,910
Judging from the clothes on the corpse,

219
00:15:06,259 --> 00:15:08,799
it might be a tomb raider
from the late Qing or early Republic.

220
00:15:08,960 --> 00:15:10,390
Judging from his posture,

221
00:15:11,030 --> 00:15:13,120
he was probably trying
to crawl in through this hole.

222
00:15:14,510 --> 00:15:16,320
But those vines trapped him.

223
00:15:17,750 --> 00:15:19,480
He used a centipede climbing ladder.

224
00:15:20,360 --> 00:15:22,150
That's Ridge Movers' style.

225
00:15:23,150 --> 00:15:25,080
Ridge Movers? That's odd.

226
00:15:25,790 --> 00:15:27,198
I heard Ridge Movers once destroyed

227
00:15:27,209 --> 00:15:28,480
Genghis Khan's side tomb

228
00:15:29,030 --> 00:15:30,390
and were hunted by his descendants.

229
00:15:30,600 --> 00:15:32,006
Their line's been fading ever since.

230
00:15:32,720 --> 00:15:34,390
They were driven out
of the Central Plains

231
00:15:34,670 --> 00:15:36,303
and forced to flee
all the way to Europe.

232
00:15:36,840 --> 00:15:38,390
They came back for this tomb.

233
00:15:38,910 --> 00:15:40,150
It must be something big.

234
00:15:41,390 --> 00:15:42,230
Come on up.

235
00:15:43,780 --> 00:15:44,630
Hold on to it.

236
00:15:44,630 --> 00:15:45,510
Slowly.

237
00:16:00,880 --> 00:16:03,980
♪A tiny ark sails;
the sky opens its eyes♪

238
00:16:05,660 --> 00:16:09,340
♪Stillness in motion,
the earth plays its chord♪

239
00:16:10,400 --> 00:16:14,980
♪A leaf falls;
we cross through time and space♪

240
00:16:15,130 --> 00:16:22,130
♪In a blink, all things rest
upon our hands♪

241
00:16:22,690 --> 00:16:33,710
♪La la♪

242
00:16:40,460 --> 00:16:42,450
♪No line divides the border♪

243
00:16:42,890 --> 00:16:45,230
♪Nothing limits your performance♪

244
00:16:45,230 --> 00:16:47,600
♪Everything shows perfect harmony♪

245
00:16:47,600 --> 00:16:50,290
♪Love circles the sky,
the earth, and our faith♪

246
00:16:51,790 --> 00:16:53,500
♪Hey hey hey♪

247
00:16:54,830 --> 00:16:56,650
♪Hey hey hey♪

248
00:16:59,300 --> 00:17:00,300
♪Hey hey♪

249
00:17:00,450 --> 00:17:01,450
♪Hey hey♪

250
00:17:02,910 --> 00:17:03,990
♪Hey hey♪

251
00:17:05,620 --> 00:17:09,820
♪Step into the galaxy of colors♪

252
00:17:10,410 --> 00:17:14,120
♪Stars connect our hearts as one♪

253
00:17:16,400 --> 00:17:18,620
♪No difference between you and me♪

254
00:17:18,900 --> 00:17:21,230
♪No lead or side role on this stage♪

255
00:17:21,230 --> 00:17:23,440
♪A perfect life is something we share♪

256
00:17:23,660 --> 00:17:25,940
♪Love declares across the sky and earth♪

257
00:17:26,870 --> 00:17:31,660
♪Huo la yi ya, huo la yi ya♪

258
00:17:31,660 --> 00:17:36,510
♪Time and space go beyond all bounds♪

259
00:17:36,510 --> 00:17:41,360
♪Huo la yi ya, huo la yi ya♪

260
00:17:41,360 --> 00:17:43,450
♪This is our world♪

261
00:17:43,450 --> 00:17:48,480
♪Shining lives bring the change♪

262
00:17:53,010 --> 00:17:55,570
♪In a blink, to forever♪
